                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The ayngavhaul imparts blasphemous thoughts into the minds of all non-devil creatures within a @Template[type:burst|distance:20] up to 60 feet away. An affected creature takes @Damage[2d10[mental]|options:area-damage] damage plus @Damage[2d10[spirit]|options:area-damage] damage and must attempt a @Check[will|dc:33|options:area-effect,damaging-effect,inflicts:slowed] save. Affected creatures gain a cumulative +1 circumstance bonus (up to a total of +4) to saves against all future attempts to Herald Heresy for 1 minute, as they become inured to the blasphemies.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and becomes temporarily immune for 1 hour.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 2}.</p>"
                },
